c. California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA)<br>
If you are a resident of the state of California, under the California Consumer Privacy Act (California Civil Code §1798.100 et. (seq., as amended from time to time, the “CCPA”)), you have the following rights:

Access. The right to know or request that a business disclose what Visitor Personal Information of yours that it collects, uses, discloses and sells.
Deletion. The right to request that a business delete Visitor Personal Information collected or maintained by the business.
Sale/Transfer. The right to opt-out of the sale or transfer of Visitor Personal Information for consideration by a business (aka “Do Not Sell My Information”).
Discrimination. The right not to receive discriminatory or differentiated treatment by a business because you exercised a right conferred by the CCPA.
To submit a right to know, delete or opt-out (aka Do Not Sell My Information) request regarding Visitor Personal Information, click here, or call toll-free: (888) 213-4233. You may only make a verifiable customer request for access twice within a 12-month period. We will only use Visitor Personal Information provided in a verifiable consumer request to verify the requestor’s identity or authority to make the request.

If you submit a right to know or deletion request, BambooHR will attempt to verify your identity with a reasonably high degree of certainty. BambooHR will require you to sign a declaration attesting to your identity. Please see below for information on how to submit an authorized request on another’s behalf. If BambooHR cannot verify your identity, we will, in accordance with its obligations under the CCPA, decline to comply with your request.

